</note><note id="fs-id1167063595158" class="ap-science-practices ost-reading-discard"><label>Science Practice Connection for AP<sup>®</sup> Courses</label>
<note id="fs-id1167063590014" class="ost-assignable ost-sciprac-activity ost-tag-lo-apbio-ch14-s03-aplo-3-3">
<para id="fs-id1167067193127">Design (but do not implement) an experiment to test the three models of DNA replication. Summarize the results you would expect if each of the three models of DNA replication were correct. Assume you have access in a laboratory to the following: an experimental organism such as <emphasis effect="italics">E. coli</emphasis>, an unlimited variety of isotopes, test tube and centrifuge, and organic growth media.</para>
</note>
